description:
Japanese title: Tamashii no Katachi 〜Saikyō Shokunin Shutain Tōjō?〜 (魂のかたち 〜最強職人シュタイン登場?〜)

Maka, Soul, Black Star, and Tsubaki tangle with the mad scientist responsible for turning Sid into a zombie - the amazingly powerful Dr. Stein!
name: Shape of the Soul – Enter the Ultimate Meister Stein?

description:
Japanese title: Uwasa no Shinnyūsei! 〜Omoide Ippai, Kiddo no Shibusen Hatsu Tōkō?〜 (噂の新入生! 〜想い出いっぱい、キッドの死武専初登校?〜)

Death the Kid shows up for his first day at Death Weapon Meister Academy, and Black Star and Soul decide to welcome him with closed fists instead of open arms.
name: The New Student – Kid's First Day at the Academy, Will It Be an Entrance to Remember?

description:
Japanese title: Kokketsu no Kyōfu 〜Kurona no Naka ni Buki ga Iru?〜 (黒血の恐怖 〜クロナの中に武器がいる?〜)

Maka and Soul’s trip to Italy turns ugly when they run into Crona and Ragnarok, a Meister and Weapon team that shares a highly unusual bond.
name: Black-blooded Terror – There's a Weapon inside Crona?

description:
Japanese title: Majo Medyūsa 〜Ōinaru Waruki Tamashii o Motsu Mono?〜 (魔女メデューサ 〜大いなる凶き魂を持つ者?〜)

Soul is seriously injured and Maka’s fading fast. Death Scythe and Dr. Stein step in to make sure the weird rampage of Crona and Ragnarok comes to an end.
name: Medusa the Witch – The One Who Possesses a Great Evil Soul?

description:
Japanese title: Seiken Densetsu 〜Kiddo to Burakku Sutā no Daibōken?〜 (聖剣伝説 〜キッドとブラック☆スターの大冒険?〜)

Black Star and Death the Kid discover the worst part of searching for the legendary Excalibur: finding the legendary Excalibur.
name: Legend of the Holy Sword – Kid and Black Star's Great Adventure?

description:
Japanese title: Yōtō Masamune 〜Yabure Tamashii Hyōi, Ame ni Utau Kokoro?〜 (妖刀マサムネ 〜破れ魂憑依、雨に詠う心?〜)

Black Star and Tsubaki face Masamune, and as the battle against the dark Weapon escalates, it becomes clear that Tsubaki must finish the fight alone.
name: The Enchanted Sword Masamune – Break the Soul Possession: A Heart Sings in the Rain?

description:
Japanese title: Tsubaki no Hana 〜Kanashimi o Koeta Saki ni Aru Mono?〜 (椿の花 〜悲しみを越えた先にあるもの?〜)

Black Star and Tsubaki will claim their first soul if they defeat Masamune - but if Tsubaki falls, she will be absorbed forever by her powerful and bitter brother.
name: Tsubaki, the Camellia Blossom – What Lies Beyond the Grief?

description:
Japanese title: Kyōfu ni Makenai Yūki 〜Maka Arubān no Ichidai Kesshin?〜 (恐怖に負けない勇気 〜マカ=アルバーンの一大決心?〜)

After seeing Soul’s new scar, Maka searches for the strength to keep her partner safe. It could be a tough prospect - the witch responsible for the wound is dangerously close.
name: Courage That Beats Out Fear - Maka Albarn's Great Resolution?

description:
Japanese title: Magan no Otoko 〜Sōru to Maka, Zure Yuku Tamashii no Hachō?〜 (魔眼の男 〜ソウルとマカ、ズレゆく魂の波長?〜)

Maka and Soul are having trouble syncing their wavelengths, a fact that proves problematic when they find themselves fighting an immortal werewolf.
name: The Man with the Magic Eye - Soul and Maka's Diverging Soul Wavelength?

description:
Japanese title: Chō Hikkishiken 〜Dokidoki, Wakuwaku, Sowasowa, Usōn?〜 (超筆記試験 〜ドキドキ、ワクワク、ソワソワ、ウソーン?〜)

There’s an important exam coming, and legend says whoever gets the highest grade is destined to reach Death Scythe. Maka won’t settle for anything but the best score.
name: The Super Written Exam - Heart-Pounding, Reeling, and Restless. You're Kidding!?

description: Leo takes the Turtles to train in the woods in an advanced ninja ritual where they must overcome their weaknesses and face their greatest enemies in order to become true ninja.
name: Vision Quest

has_staff_review.name: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles Episode 308 - "Vision Quest"

name: Alone Together

description:
Japanese title: Tamashii o Kū Kuroki Ryū 〜Okubyō Rizu to Yukai na Nakama-tachi?〜 (魂を食う黒き龍 〜臆病リズと愉快な仲間たち?〜)

Death the Kid and the Thompson sisters board a ghost ship full of human souls. After facing the vessel’s demented captain, true evil unfurls its wings.
name: The Soul Eating Black Dragon - Scaredy-cat Liz and Her Merry Friends?

description:
Japanese title: Gekitō! Yūreisen 〜Boku no Atama no Naka no Jigoku?〜 (激闘! 幽霊船 〜ボクの頭の中の地獄?〜)

Unsettled by something he heard on the ghost ship, Kid asks his father an unimaginable question. Dr. Stein has his own questions regarding Medusa’s qualifications as a nurse.

See-Saw to Arkansas/Creepy Trip to Lemon Twist

description:
Japanese title: Seiken Densetsu Tsū 〜Nomu, Utsu, Kau, Ittoku?〜 (聖剣伝説2 〜飲む、打つ、買う、いっとく?〜)

Ox Ford triumphantly raises Excalibur to the heavens! Instead of fame and glory, he gets a painfully detailed account of Excalibur’s past lives and loves.

A party to celebrate the founding of Death Weapon Meister Academy erupts into chaos when Medusa and her minions unleash an assault on the school.
name: The Eve Party Nightmare - And So the Curtain Rises?
